This lookup was added for ITPR002957 FEP 2012 for Rebates.
This expression will evaluate the response from the LKP_RCIT_PMCY_NTWK results and possibly change the BCA SPCL_DRUG_CD value being written out.
If the lookup returns a Rebate ID, then that means this claims RBAT_ID/PHCY_NTWK_ID/DSPN_DT (range) was found in the RCIT_PMCY_NTWK table, and therefore the BCA SPCL_DRUG_CD value needs to be overridden to a '4'.

SHORTCUT.COMMENTS:
This lookup was added for ITPR002957 FEP 2012 for Rebates.
This expression will evaluate the response from the LKP_RCIT_PMCY_NTWK results and possibly change the BCA SPCL_DRUG_CD value being written out.
If the lookup returns a SPCL_DRUG_CD then that means this claims RBAT_ID/PHCY_NTWK_ID/DSPN_DT (range) was found in the RCIT_PMCY_NTWK table, and therefore the BCA SPCL_DRUG_CD value needs to be overridden to the value returned. Otherwise, the value will be what is calculated from the EXP_ALL_Expressions transformation.

This lookup was added for ITPR002957 FEP 2012 for Rebates.

If the claim fields match the a row in the lookup, use the SPCL_DRUG_CD on the lookup for the target field value on BCA.
SHORTCUT.NAME: LKP_RCIT_SPCL_NTWK
